BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (CHAPTER 2: CBT THOUGHT RECORDS & WORKSHEETS) Tj ET
54 684.0 m 558 684.0 l 0.5 w S
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 658.2 Td (Introduction to Cognitive Behavioral Therapy) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 630.4 Td (Cognitive Behavioral Therapy \(CBT\) is the gold standard treatment for anxiety disorders.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 616.4 Td (It is based on the principle that our thoughts, feelings, and behaviors are all) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 602.4 Td (interconnected. By changing the way we think about situations, we can change how we feel) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 588.4 Td (and what we do.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 564.6 Td (The CBT model shows that it is not situations themselves that cause anxiety, but rather) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 550.6 Td (our interpretation of those situations. Two people can face the exact same situation and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 536.6 Td (have completely different emotional responses because they interpret the situation) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 522.6 Td (differently.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 498.8 Td (Thought records are the cornerstone tool of CBT. They help you identify, examine, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 484.8 Td (restructure the automatic negative thoughts that fuel your anxiety. With regular practice,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 470.8 Td (you will develop the ability to catch distorted thoughts in real-time and replace them) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 456.8 Td (with more balanced perspectives.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 427.0 Td (Common Cognitive Distortions) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 399.2 Td (These are thinking patterns that seem true but actually distort reality in) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 385.2 Td (anxiety-provoking ways:) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 357.4 Td (1. Catastrophizing) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 341.4 Td (Assuming the worst possible outcome will definitely happen. Example: A headache means you) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 327.4 Td (have a brain tumor. Being late to work means you will be fired.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 299.6 Td (2. All-or-Nothing Thinking) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 283.6 Td (Seeing things in black and white with no middle ground. If something is not perfect, it is) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 269.6 Td (a complete failure. Example: If you make one mistake in a presentation, the entire thing) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 255.6 Td (was terrible.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 227.8 Td (3. Mind Reading) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 211.8 Td (Assuming you know what others are thinking, usually that they are judging you negatively.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 197.8 Td (Example: They did not text back because they think I am annoying.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 170.0 Td (4. Fortune Telling) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 154.0 Td (Predicting negative outcomes with certainty before they happen. Example: I just know this) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 140.0 Td (interview is going to go badly.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 112.2 Td (5. Emotional Reasoning) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
