BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (CHAPTER 3: BREATHING & GROUNDING TECHNIQUES) Tj ET
54 684.0 m 558 684.0 l 0.5 w S
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 658.2 Td (Why Breathing Matters) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 630.4 Td (When anxiety activates your fight-or-flight response, one of the first things that changes) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 616.4 Td (is your breathing pattern. You begin to breathe faster and shallower, taking in more) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 602.4 Td (oxygen than your body needs. This hyperventilation actually makes anxiety symptoms worse) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 588.4 Td (by causing dizziness, tingling, and chest tightness.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 564.6 Td (Controlled breathing is the fastest way to activate your parasympathetic nervous system,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 550.6 Td (which is responsible for the relaxation response. By deliberately slowing and deepening) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 536.6 Td (your breath, you send a signal to your brain that says you are safe, and your body begins) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 522.6 Td (to calm down within minutes.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 492.8 Td (Technique 1: 4-7-8 Breathing) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 465.0 Td (This technique was developed by Dr. Andrew Weil and is one of the most effective methods) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 451.0 Td (for rapid anxiety relief. It works by extending your exhale, which stimulates the vagus) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 437.0 Td (nerve.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 409.2 Td (Instructions:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 393.2 Td (- Sit comfortably with your back straight) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 379.2 Td (- Place the tip of your tongue against the ridge behind your upper front teeth) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 365.2 Td (- Exhale completely through your mouth, making a whoosh sound) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 351.2 Td (- Close your mouth and INHALE quietly through your nose for 4 counts) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 337.2 Td (- HOLD your breath for 7 counts) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 323.2 Td (- EXHALE completely through your mouth for 8 counts \(whoosh sound\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 309.2 Td (- This is one complete breath cycle) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 295.2 Td (- Repeat for 4 full cycles \(work up to 8 cycles over time\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 271.4 Td (Practice Schedule: Do this exercise twice daily - once in the morning and once before bed.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 257.4 Td (Also use it any time you feel anxiety rising.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 233.6 Td (My 4-7-8 Practice Log:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 219.6 Td (Day 1 - Morning: ___ Evening: ___ Anxiety Level Before/After: ___/___) Tj ET
