BT /F1 10 Tf 54 720.0 Td (Used by Navy SEALs to remain calm under extreme pressure. This technique is excellent for) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 706.0 Td (acute anxiety or panic situations because of its simplicity and effectiveness.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 678.2 Td (Instructions:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 662.2 Td (- Visualize a square or box in your mind) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 648.2 Td (- INHALE for 4 counts \(trace up the left side of the box\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 634.2 Td (- HOLD for 4 counts \(trace across the top\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 620.2 Td (- EXHALE for 4 counts \(trace down the right side\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 606.2 Td (- HOLD for 4 counts \(trace across the bottom\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 592.2 Td (- Repeat for 5-10 minutes or until calm) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 562.4 Td (Technique 3: Diaphragmatic \(Belly\) Breathing) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 534.6 Td (Most anxious people breathe into their chest. Diaphragmatic breathing engages the belly,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 520.6 Td (activating deeper relaxation and better oxygen exchange.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 492.8 Td (Instructions:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 476.8 Td (- Lie down or sit comfortably) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 462.8 Td (- Place one hand on your chest and one on your belly) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 448.8 Td (- Breathe in slowly through your nose for 4 counts) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 434.8 Td (- Your belly should rise while your chest stays relatively still) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 420.8 Td (- Exhale slowly through pursed lips for 6 counts) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 406.8 Td (- Feel your belly fall back down) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 392.8 Td (- Practice for 5-10 minutes, twice daily) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 363.0 Td (Grounding Technique 1: The 5-4-3-2-1 Method) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 335.2 Td (This powerful technique works by redirecting your attention from anxious thoughts to your) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 321.2 Td (immediate physical environment. It engages all five senses to anchor you in the present) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 307.2 Td (moment.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 279.4 Td (Instructions:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 263.4 Td (When you feel anxiety rising or a panic attack beginning, work through these steps:) Tj ET
