BT /F2 12 Tf 54 558.6 Td (Grounding Technique 2: Progressive Muscle Relaxation) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 530.8 Td (PMR works by systematically tensing and then releasing muscle groups throughout your body.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 516.8 Td (This teaches you to recognize the difference between tension and relaxation, and releases) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 502.8 Td (stored physical anxiety.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 475.0 Td (Full Body PMR Script \(15-20 minutes\):) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 449.2 Td (For each muscle group: Tense for 5 seconds, then release for 15 seconds. Notice the) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 435.2 Td (contrast between tension and relaxation.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 411.4 Td (- FEET: Curl your toes tightly... hold... release and notice the relaxation) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 397.4 Td (- CALVES: Point your toes up toward shins... hold... release) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 383.4 Td (- THIGHS: Squeeze your thigh muscles... hold... release) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 369.4 Td (- BUTTOCKS: Clench your glutes... hold... release) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 355.4 Td (- STOMACH: Tighten your abdominal muscles... hold... release) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 341.4 Td (- CHEST: Take a deep breath and hold... hold... exhale and release) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 327.4 Td (- HANDS: Make tight fists... hold... release and spread fingers) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 313.4 Td (- FOREARMS: Flex your wrists back... hold... release) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 299.4 Td (- BICEPS: Curl your arms up tightly... hold... release) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 285.4 Td (- SHOULDERS: Shrug shoulders up to ears... hold... release and drop) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 271.4 Td (- NECK: Gently press head back... hold... release) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 257.4 Td (- FACE: Scrunch all facial muscles... hold... release) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 243.4 Td (- FOREHEAD: Raise eyebrows high... hold... release) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 219.6 Td (After completing all muscle groups, take 3 deep breaths and notice how your entire body) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 205.6 Td (feels different from when you started.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 175.8 Td (Grounding Technique 3: Cold Water Reset) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 148.0 Td (The diving reflex is a powerful physiological response that immediately slows your heart) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 134.0 Td (rate and calms your nervous system. It works by triggering the vagus nerve through) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 120.0 Td (temperature change.) Tj ET
endstream
