BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (CHAPTER 4: WORRY MANAGEMENT SYSTEM) Tj ET
54 684.0 m 558 684.0 l 0.5 w S
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 658.2 Td (Understanding Worry) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 630.4 Td (Worry is a cognitive process where your mind repeatedly cycles through potential negative) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 616.4 Td (outcomes. Unlike productive problem-solving, worry does not lead to solutions. Instead, it) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 602.4 Td (keeps you trapped in a loop of what if scenarios that increase anxiety without resolving) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 588.4 Td (anything.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 564.6 Td (Research shows that 85% of things people worry about never actually happen. Of the 15%) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 550.6 Td (that do occur, 79% of people report handling the situation better than they expected. This) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 536.6 Td (means that 97% of what you worry about is either unlikely to happen or more manageable) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 522.6 Td (than you think.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 498.8 Td (The key is not to eliminate worry entirely, which is impossible, but to contain it,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 484.8 Td (evaluate it, and redirect your mental energy toward things you can actually control.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 455.0 Td (The Worry Decision Tree) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 427.2 Td (When you notice yourself worrying, ask these questions in order:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 403.4 Td (Step 1: Is this worry about something I can control?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 389.4 Td (   YES -> Go to Step 2) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 375.4 Td (   NO -> Practice acceptance. Use grounding. Let it go.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 351.6 Td (Step 2: Can I take action on this RIGHT NOW?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 337.6 Td (   YES -> Take one small action immediately) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 323.6 Td (   NO -> Schedule it in your worry time. Write it down. Move on.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 299.8 Td (Step 3: What is the smallest possible action I can take?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 285.8 Td (   Write it here: _________________________________________________) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 271.8 Td (   When will I do it? _____________________________________________) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 242.0 Td (Scheduled Worry Time) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 214.2 Td (One of the most effective worry management strategies is to designate a specific time and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 200.2 Td (place for worrying. Outside of this window, you postpone all worries to your scheduled) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 186.2 Td (time.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 158.4 Td (How to implement:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 142.4 Td (- Choose a 15-20 minute window each day \(not before bed\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 128.4 Td (- Choose a specific location \(not your bedroom\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 114.4 Td (- When worries arise outside this time, write them down and postpone) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 100.4 Td (- During worry time, worry intentionally about your list) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 86.4 Td (- When the timer ends, close your worry list and move on) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
