BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (CHAPTER 6: COPING STRATEGIES TOOLKIT) Tj ET
54 684.0 m 558 684.0 l 0.5 w S
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 664.2 Td (Having a diverse toolkit of coping strategies is essential because different situations) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 650.2 Td (call for different approaches. What works during a panic attack is different from what) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 636.2 Td (helps with chronic background worry. Build your personal toolkit by trying each strategy) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 622.2 Td (and noting which ones work best for you.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 592.4 Td (CATEGORY 1: Physical Strategies \(Body-Based\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 564.6 Td (- 1. Go for a brisk 10-minute walk outside) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 550.6 Td (- 2. Do 20 jumping jacks or burpees to burn off adrenaline) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 536.6 Td (- 3. Take a cold shower or splash cold water on your face) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 522.6 Td (- 4. Stretch your neck, shoulders, and back for 5 minutes) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 508.6 Td (- 5. Practice progressive muscle relaxation from head to toe) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 494.6 Td (- 6. Dance to your favorite upbeat song for 3 minutes) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 480.6 Td (- 7. Do yoga or gentle stretching for 15 minutes) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 466.6 Td (- 8. Squeeze a stress ball or fidget toy) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 452.6 Td (- 9. Hug someone or a pillow tightly for 20 seconds) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 438.6 Td (- 10. Chew gum or eat something crunchy mindfully) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 408.8 Td (CATEGORY 2: Mental Strategies \(Thought-Based\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 381.0 Td (- 11. Name your anxiety as a character \(Hello, Worry Monster\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 367.0 Td (- 12. Count backward from 100 by 7s) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 353.0 Td (- 13. Name 5 countries, 5 animals, 5 colors in your head) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 339.0 Td (- 14. Visualize your safe place in vivid detail) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 325.0 Td (- 15. Repeat a calming mantra: This feeling is temporary) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 311.0 Td (- 16. Challenge the thought: What evidence supports this?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 297.0 Td (- 17. Ask: Will this matter in 5 years? 5 months? 5 weeks?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 283.0 Td (- 18. Imagine advising a friend with the same worry) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 269.0 Td (- 19. Rate your anxiety 1-10 and check back in 10 minutes) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 255.0 Td (- 20. Write the worry down and physically put it away) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 225.2 Td (CATEGORY 3: Sensory Strategies \(Five Senses\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 197.4 Td (- 21. Light a scented candle or use essential oils \(lavender\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 183.4 Td (- 22. Listen to calming music or nature sounds) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 169.4 Td (- 23. Look at photos that make you feel happy and safe) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 155.4 Td (- 24. Wrap yourself in a weighted blanket or heavy comforter) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 141.4 Td (- 25. Drink herbal tea slowly, noticing temperature and flavor) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 127.4 Td (- 26. Take a warm bath with epsom salts) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 113.4 Td (- 27. Pet an animal and focus on the texture of their fur) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 99.4 Td (- 28. Eat dark chocolate slowly, savoring each bite) Tj ET
